 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-54y","title":"Watch: Alert thresholds and notifications","description":"## Overview
Implement alert thresholds that highlight or notify users when usage approaches limits.

## Background & Rationale
The key value of watch mode is proactive alerting. Users want to know BEFORE they hit a rate limit, not after. Alert thresholds let users configure when they want to be warned.

## Technical Approach

### 1. Alert Configuration
```rust
// CLI args
#[derive(Debug, Args)]
pub struct UsageArgs {
    // ... existing ...

    /// Alert when any providers remaining percent drops below this threshold.
    #[arg(long, default_value = "20")]
    pub alert_threshold: f64,

    /// Play terminal bell on alert (BEL character).
    #[arg(long)]
    pub alert_bell: bool,

    /// Run command when alert threshold crossed.
    #[arg(long)]
    pub alert_command: Option<String>,
}
```

### 2. Alert State Tracking
```rust
// In cli/watch.rs
pub struct AlertState {
    /// Providers that have crossed alert threshold.
    pub alerted_providers: HashSet<Provider>,
    /// Last alert time (for rate limiting).
    pub last_alert_at: Option<chrono::DateTime<Utc>>,
}

impl AlertState {
    pub fn check_alerts(
        &mut self,
        results: &[ProviderPayload],
        threshold: f64,
    ) -> Vec<Alert> {
        let mut alerts = Vec::new();

        for payload in results {
            let provider = Provider::from_cli_name(&payload.provider).ok();

            // Check primary window
            if let Some(primary) = &payload.usage.primary {
                let remaining = primary.remaining_percent();
                if remaining < threshold {
                    if let Some(p) = provider {
                        if !self.alerted_providers.contains(&p) {
                            alerts.push(Alert {
                                provider: p,
                                window: "primary",
                                remaining_percent: remaining,
                                reset_description: primary.reset_description.clone(),
                            });
                            self.alerted_providers.insert(p);
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
            // Similar for secondary, tertiary...
        }

        alerts
    }

    pub fn clear_recovered(&mut self, results: &[ProviderPayload], threshold: f64) {
        // Remove providers from alerted set if they have recovered above threshold
        // This allows re-alerting if they drop below again
    }
}
```

### 3. Alert Display
```rust
fn format_alert(alert: &Alert, no_color: bool) -> String {
    let icon = if no_color { "!" } else { "🚨" };
    format!(
        "{} {} is at {:.0}% remaining ({})",
        icon,
        alert.provider.display_name(),
        alert.remaining_percent,
        alert.reset_description.as_deref().unwrap_or("unknown reset")
    )
}
```

### 4. Terminal Bell
```rust
fn play_bell() {
    print!("\x07"); // BEL character
    io::stdout().flush().ok();
}
```

### 5. Alert Command Execution
```rust
async fn run_alert_command(command: &str, alert: &Alert) -> Result<()> {
    // Environment variables for the command
    let output = tokio::process::Command::new("sh")
        .arg("-c")
        .arg(command)
        .env("CAUT_ALERT_PROVIDER", alert.provider.cli_name())
        .env("CAUT_ALERT_REMAINING", alert.remaining_percent.to_string())
        .env("CAUT_ALERT_WINDOW", alert.window)
        .output()
        .await?;

    if !output.status.success() {
        tracing::warn!("Alert command failed: {}", String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stderr));
    }

    Ok(())
}
```

### 6. Alert Rate Limiting
```rust
impl AlertState {
    /// Minimum time between alerts (avoid spam).
    const ALERT_COOLDOWN: Duration = Duration::from_secs(60);

    pub fn should_alert(&self) -> bool {
        match self.last_alert_at {
            Some(t) => Utc::now() - t > chrono::Duration::from_std(Self::ALERT_COOLDOWN).unwrap(),
            None => true,
        }
    }
}
```

