 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-5gn","title":"Creds: Implement JWT expiration and token health checking","description":"## Summary
Implement detection of expiring, expired, or invalid JWT tokens and OAuth credentials.

## Background
LLM provider credentials expire silently. Users often don't know their tokens are invalid until fetches fail. We should proactively warn about:
1. JWT tokens nearing expiration
2. OAuth refresh tokens expiring
3. API keys that have been revoked
4. Cookies/sessions approaching expiry

## Technical Design

### JWT Expiration Checking
```rust
use jsonwebtoken::{decode, DecodingKey, Validation, Algorithm};

pub struct JwtHealthChecker;

impl JwtHealthChecker {
    /// Check JWT health without validating signature
    pub fn check(&self, token: &str) -> JwtHealth {
        // Decode without verification (we just want claims)
        let mut validation = Validation::default();
        validation.insecure_disable_signature_validation();
        validation.validate_exp = false;

        match decode::<Claims>(token, &DecodingKey::from_secret(&[]), &validation) {
            Ok(data) => {
                let now = Utc::now().timestamp();
                let exp = data.claims.exp;
                let remaining = exp - now;

                if remaining < 0 {
                    JwtHealth::Expired { expired_at: exp }
                } else if remaining < 3600 {
                    JwtHealth::ExpiringSoon { 
                        expires_in: Duration::seconds(remaining),
                        expires_at: exp,
                    }
                } else if remaining < 86400 {
                    JwtHealth::ExpiringToday {
                        expires_in: Duration::seconds(remaining),
                    }
                } else {
                    JwtHealth::Valid {
                        expires_in: Duration::seconds(remaining),
                    }
                }
            }
            Err(_) => JwtHealth::Invalid,
        }
    }
}

#[derive(Debug)]
pub enum JwtHealth {
    Valid { expires_in: Duration },
    ExpiringToday { expires_in: Duration },
    ExpiringSoon { expires_in: Duration, expires_at: i64 },
    Expired { expired_at: i64 },
    Invalid,
}
```

### OAuth Token Health
```rust
pub struct OAuthHealthChecker;

impl OAuthHealthChecker {
    /// Check OAuth token file health
    pub fn check(&self, auth_file: &Path) -> OAuthHealth {
        let auth: OAuthAuth = self.read_auth_file(auth_file)?;

        // Check access token
        let access_health = self.check_jwt(&auth.access_token);

        // Check refresh token (usually longer-lived)
        let refresh_health = auth.refresh_token
            .as_ref()
            .map(|t| self.check_jwt(t));

        OAuthHealth {
            access: access_health,
            refresh: refresh_health,
            can_refresh: matches!(refresh_health, Some(JwtHealth::Valid { .. })),
        }
    }
}
```

### Cookie Session Health
```rust
pub struct CookieHealthChecker;

impl CookieHealthChecker {
    /// Check browser cookie session health
    pub fn check(&self, cookie_file: &Path) -> CookieHealth {
        let cookies = self.read_cookie_file(cookie_file)?;

        // Find auth cookies
        let session_cookie = cookies.iter()
            .find(|c| c.name == "sessionKey" || c.name.contains("session"));

        match session_cookie {
            Some(cookie) => {
                if cookie.expired() {
                    CookieHealth::Expired
                } else if cookie.expires_within(Duration::hours(24)) {
                    CookieHealth::ExpiringSoon { expires_in: cookie.remaining_time() }
                } else {
                    CookieHealth::Valid
                }
            }
            None => CookieHealth::Missing,
        }
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] JWT expiration detection works correctly
- [ ] Handle JWTs without exp claim gracefully
- [ ] OAuth access/refresh token health checked
- [ ] Cookie expiration checked where applicable
- [ ] Handle malformed tokens gracefully
- [ ] Unit tests with sample tokens at various expiration states

## Token Sources by Provider
| Provider | Token Type | Location |
|----------|------------|----------|
| Claude | OAuth JWT | ~/.config/caut/claude/auth.json |
| Claude | Cookies | varies by browser |
| Codex | OAuth JWT | ~/.codex/auth.json |
| OpenRouter | API Key | env or config (no expiry) |

## Dependencies
- None (foundational)
- Used by auth freshness tracking

## Security Notes
- Never log token values
- Don't validate signatures (we don't have the keys)
- Handle errors without leaking token info
